{
  "stem": "11964.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My-- my understanding of anti-Semitism was almost part of my life.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We knew the reason we went to a Jewish school is because they wouldn't let us go to a non-- to a Gentile school.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We knew the reason that we had to stay indoors, for example, at the time of religious processions, Catholic religious processions, is because we didn't want to incite the non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We knew, for example, that when there was a non-Jewish, a Gentile, funeral, for example, we would try to stay away because we are not-- we are not desired.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Our presence would not be desired there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there were certain-- some-- some were even superstitious elements into-- inculcated into us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we knew that they existed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we knew that that was part of our lives.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we just accepted it, because this was our modus vivendi.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had no other choice.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When did you first realize that you were surrounded by danger?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, actually, I would like to track back a little bit.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- I went to the university, to the Jagiellonian University in Krakow, to study after I was graduated from high school.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the first thing I knew, that I couldn't apply to any-- to-- to any department I wanted.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I knew-- and I knew that many of my friends and my sister's friends who wanted to become doctors and lawyers had no chance of studying in Poland.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Therefore, many, many of the people that I knew would go to France or would go to Belgium, for example.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "A friend of mine went to Belgium to study engineering.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My sister's friends went to Paris to-- to study medicine or to study dentistry.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, in Poland, we could not gain access to any of these professional schools.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
